As surprising as it may seem, I accidentally deleted our entire team from Onshape, causing all of our documents to scatter among past members.
We have lost our team organization that has been existing for years, so we really need to recover this as soon as possible.
I would really appreciate if anyone can help me on this.

@RachelKim I know your not thinking of it right this second while folks look into undoing whatever was done (and in the US its late anyways and time to sleep), but this would also be a good educational post and lessons learned!

Consider over the next day or 2 while your mind is fresh taking the time to write down your experience, the steps you took, and reflect on how this happened. It could be that its too easy to occur and there need to be more safeguards! It could be that you though there was no way your team would give you such power and this delete everything button cannot possibly work - but you pressed it to see what would happen.

Regardless of the reason, reflect on how/why and consider publishing that reflection if appropriate to have others learn though your mistakes or process.

Preface this with - I have been here before, I accidentally issued a command in AIX (consider it the IBM version of Linux) that attempted to delete literally the entire operating system from the disk and being Linux there’s no confirmation. Standard practice in IT, always name test or dev environments with a portion of the name that signifies it is non-production but if you’re not paying attention (like me that day) accidents can happen

Ever since that day when I’ve said to myself “what’s the worst that could happen?” I think quite carefully.
